						               													<description>Wobuga comes from WOrd BUilding GAme.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It includes 72 letters: 6 each for A, E, I, O; 4 each for U, Y; 2 each of all other letters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To start, the letters are stirred face down, and each player draws 5 letters. A turn consists of drawing a letter and then either making a word out of one's hand, or adding one or more letters to words already on the table without rearranging their order.  After playing, a player draws again and continues playing until announcing &amp;quot;I am thru&amp;quot;, and the turn goes to the left. One can also make a sentence out of their own words, after which those words cannot be further altered. When a turn is over and other players see plays they could have done, they say &amp;quot;Wobuga&amp;quot; and can make the play for them and score the points they could have scored.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Points scored are: 5 points for each letter played during one's turn, 10 points for each word of a sentence, and 25 points for making the word &amp;quot;Wobuga&amp;quot;.  The highest score when all the letters are used wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is also a solitaire mode where a player takes repeated turns and tries to use all the letters.  Also, Wobuga Rush, where two players each play with a half deck in solitaire mode, and play through all their letters.  Each player gets 5 points for each letter not used, and -10 points for being the first to say &amp;quot;I am thru&amp;quot;; the lower score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
